<head>SAUCE</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">調味汁</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SPICY LIQUID PUT ON DRY FOOD.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general word for a spicy meat sauce is jiàng 醬.</p>
<p>2. Zū 菹 / 葅 refers to minced meat sauce without bones, and made of any meat, occasionally even that of humans.</p>
<p>3. Hái 醢 refers to pickled meat sauce with any kind of meat, with or without bones.</p>
<p>4. Ní 臡 refers to pickled meat sauce with meat on the bone</p>
<p>5. Láo 酪 refers to a kind of acid sauce made with rice or millet.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
